messages.content: @Max-A-Million You want this one?
Yeye
It's yours.  Last we saw Max, he was in the RV, chatting with the old woman with the white braided hair.  Zahir is on the bed recovering and Moonshine and Becca had stepped out.
Max looks to the older woman, observing her as she cleans the rabbits. "Do you know who I-... who we could speak with who can explain what's going on?"

She grins (a fearsome sight, as her teeth have seen better days) "There will be a meet very shortly where you'll learn more.  Peregrine and myself have been out dealing with the recent issues and we need to report to the pack anyway.  You'll be invited."
"...Why save us? We are worth nothing to your kind, many of us are better of dead... why us?"

**Zahir has sat down at the table to observe** She chuckles.  "You are so young!  When you have seen what I have seen, and fought who I have fought, you will learn - few are better off dead and many are more bitter for it.
We saved you because you know things that are useful to us.  And because we need your help
And you need ours."
"I'm assuming you know of the mage's request then?"

She shrugs.  "We know much, and are able to be many places - but we can't turn into flies!  We know you were approached.  We know they are dangerous.  And we know they are involved in our current troubles.  Beyond that, we felt you and we would be better off if you were here than there."
"And your motive for attacking us? The others would have been very willing to listen..."
She grins again "I attacked no one."
Max gives her a deadpan look.
She continues gutting rabbits and changes the subject. "You look famished.  I need this meat, but the blood is of no use to me.  Take all you want."
Max hesitates, glancing at the blood but not moving.
She shrugs
Zahir just observes what's going on, mainly because he doesn't know what to say
Max glances to Zahir and moves his head toward the food, motioning for the other to eat something.
Zahir was a little hesitant as well,, and just awkwardly stares at both Max and the woman until something happens
*To recap, Max has maybe one health box remaining (and I forget if it's temporary - if it is, and it goes away soon, he'll collapse).  Zahir took 3 lethal damage from the stake/ arrow).*
How many rabbits are there?))
12, at the moment. Divide by 3, enough for 4 Vitae.
Max eats six, and offers the others to Zahir.
GG @Max-A-Million, you just advanced to level 9!

*Clarification:  Vampires don't eat, they simply drink the blood.  The woman has stated that she doesn't need the blood, and would have to drain it anyway.  Also, a minimum of 3 rabbits would be required to attain 1 Vitae*
Ohh
I can't count lol))
Okay, so instead Zahir would drink the blood from three rabbits for a vitae then 😅
Done
Question: Can I heal so Max doesn't pass out))
That would be my recomendation.  Heal, then drink.
Max heals 4 of his lethal damage
Standing up, Max nods to the woman in thanks. Then he looks to Zahir. "I'm going to look around. You can follow me if you want too."
She nods as well
GG @OnlyaJedi, you just advanced to level 8!
Zahir nods and decides to follow Max
Thanking the old woman again, he goes outside and begins to wander around the camp, looking for someone in charge.
N, S, E, or W?
Zahir waves to the women to be nice as he goes outside with Max
Max leads the to the west of the trailer.

He shortly comes upon a man sitting on the ground in front of a table.  The table is in front of a small tent.  On the table is a blanket with a large variety of items and equipment, apparently for "sale".
Max glances over at the items, trying to see if he can idenitfy any of them

*rope, various knives, climbing equipment, brass knuckles, two old Army handguns from the '70s, three small pocket revolvers, a few boxes of assorted ammunition with worn cardboard, toolkits for mechanics etc, a few loose tools*
Zahir noticed the weapons and got excited, but he didn't want to say anything
Max notices Zahir's excitement, and begins to smile, before quickly schooling his expression. "Excuse me, sir?" Max says to the man sitting on the ground before the table.
He looks startled, like he was zoned out.  He looks up at you, "What's up?"
"Do you know where your group's leaders are?" His voice is cold, though it doesn't appear it's on purpose.
He looks confused, "What kind of leaders?"
"Any leaders who would know about any scout patrols that recently brought a group of vampires to the camp."
"Oh, scooouutts.  Sure, sure.  Actually, I had heard that our scout patrols hadn't returned.  That's weird, man.  I saw Redtail complaining earlier that she hadn't heard from the patrols yet."
"..." Max barres his teeth without thinking, his sharp fangs on display, and sighs. "Thank you for the information. Zahir, let's go."
Big eyes
Zahir nods and follows Max, looking back at the beautiful weapons for a second
Max heads toward the south side of the camp, now having linked hands with ~~his brother~~ Zahir so they wouldn't be separated.

The camp is busy.  There are many people around, and lots of conversation.  No one seems to notice them or care. They pass a number of RVs, campers, rickety tents, and treehouses.  Do they look for anything in particular or say anything to anyone?
Max tries to find people that look like they are equipped to do field work, asking them if they would happen to know about the group of vampires brought to the camp.

*two choices.  Investigation is more asking people questions and getting answers.  Survival is tracking, looking for clues, etc.  Add either INT or WIT depending on how he handles himself.  If you have another skill you'd rather use, lay it on me*
3 successes
Which choice?
Investigation and Intelligence

After asking a few questions, Max starts to notice people dressed not too dissimilarly to Peregrine gathering in small groups of 2-4, more of them as he heads in this directions.  Probably a total of 10-15 of them by this point.
Still dragging Zahir around like a parent taking their child shopping, Max walks up to the first group of 2-4 that look the closest to Peregrine's outfit.
They mostly ignore him.  They clearly have seen him, but their attitude is that of people who have "business" and it's none of his.
Can I roll using Max's presence + intimidation to get them to pay attention to him?))
Of course.  Tell me what he's specifically doing.
Max stares at them; the longer he stares the more uncomfortable they become until they can no longer ignore him.
They seem unconcerned.  He's surpsied
*surprised
Max looks to Zahir, crouches down until they are face to face, and says: "Zahir, can you go look for Becca? I need a moment."
"Sure." Zahir walks away to go find Becca
Max looks back to the group of people and sighs. "Excuse me, do you know anything about the vampires brought to camp?" ((Can I roll again this time for straight presence?))
Of course!
_...the die clatters across the table..._
Hold on I have no idea how to use the dice witch lol)))
_...the dice clatter across the table..._
No successes))
They're not impressed.  Try another tactic.  Talking to people isn't going well for Max today
I'm going to throw myself into the sun/j)))
*keep in mind, these are werewolves - I should probably be giving you a negative on your rolls to intimidate them anyway.  But today isn't Max's day, and I feel bad for him*
Max takes a deep breathe. "Okay. Fine." *Honestly, fair enough,* he thinks, *I wouldn't talk to me either.*
To calm down, he steps out and away from the camp, starting to wander on the outskirts.
Something curious happens.  Roll Wits plus Dex
_...the dice clatter across the table..._

Max finds it hard to walk far past the edge of camp.  Not like theres an invisible barrier, but every time he tries to go far, he unexpectedly finds himself walking back toward the camp.  With mental effort, he is able to sort it out, but it takes constant strain.
Max frowns. *That's... strange.* Max runs a hand through his hair.
Is Max alone by this point? Are their any other people around?))
He's alone

He's about to sit down to finally sort through his thoughts so he won't boil over, but a loud roar fills his ears and makes his stomach drop. Max's head whips toward the sound and begins running toward it as fast as he can.
***!!!RP END, ROOM OPEN!!!***

I look up and smile
"Thank you"
